The Society of Family Physicians of Nigeria (SOFPON) says its members have adopted new strategies and technologies to increase access to patients. The president of the society, Prof. Musa Dankyau, said this on Thursday in Jos during a news conference on World Family Doctor Day entitled “Family doctors: Always there to care”. He explained that members of the society had adopted strategies and technologies such as telemedicine to ensure that they were always accessible and available for consultations. (NAN) 